cs.LO, cs.AI, cs.DS, cs.PL, cs.CC 

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with solving first-order constraints. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a method for computing approximate solutions to first-order formulas, which is relevant to many AI applications. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the efficiency of the proposed method and introduces tunable quantifiers. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper modifies the first-order language and introduces new quantifiers. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is relevant as the paper discusses the difficulty of exactly solving first-order constraints and proposes an approximate solution method.
